# EDGE Glasses Firmware Docs

This folder contains the [BLE API Reference](API_REFERENCE.md) for the EDGE glasses firmware. The firmware source itself lives elsewhere; only the protocol documentation is kept here.

## The device

EDGE glasses are ESP32-PICO-D4 smart LCD glasses. They advertise over BLE as `Narbis_Edge` (service `0x00FF`, control characteristic `0xFF01`) and act as a display for app-side biofeedback: the app computes its signal and drives the lens via the breathe / static / strobe renderer. Three standalone programs (breathe, breathe+strobe, strobe) run without any app and are cycled with a magnet tap on the temple. The radio powers down after 2 minutes with no client connected — tap the magnet to re-arm advertising.

## Quick Reference

All opcode commands must be at least 2 bytes — a 1-byte write is the legacy opacity command.

| Bytes | Action |
|-------|--------|
| `[0x00-0xFF]` | Set opacity (single byte, legacy) |
| `[0xA2, pct]` | Set brightness 0-100% |
| `[0xA4, min]` | Set session duration 1-60 min |
| `[0xA5, duty]` | Static mode at duty 0-100% |
| `[0xA6, 0x00]` | Start strobe mode |
| `[0xA7, 0x00]` | Sleep now |
| `[0xAB, hz]` | Strobe frequency 1-50 Hz |
| `[0xAC, pct]` | Strobe duty 10-90% |
| `[0xB0, mode]` | Start breathe (`0x00`) / breathe+strobe (`0x01`) |
| `[0xB1, bpm]` | Breathe rate 1-30 BPM |
| `[0xBA, ms_lo, ms_hi, pct]` | Breathe sync (cycle boundary only) |
| `[0xBF, 0x00]` | Factory reset |

See the [API Reference](API_REFERENCE.md) for the complete command set, and the [published protocol doc](../docs/bluetooth-protocol.md) for the full protocol and OTA flow.

